        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 6 at 3:02PM EDT until September 6 at 3:30PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 302 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Harlem, or over
Mott Haven, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vehicles is possible. Expect wind
damage to trees and power lines.

This severe storm will be near...
Mott Haven and East Tremont around 305 PM EDT.
City Island around 310 PM EDT.
New Rochelle and Bronxville around 315 PM EDT.
Rye around 320 PM EDT.
Greenwich around 325 PM EDT.
Port Chester around 330 PM EDT.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
